The course introduces classical and newer paradigms of media and communication research, their development and use in European and American research traditions. In the seminars the theories are applied to the Estonian media context as well as to different research problems.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to give an overview of the main theoretical approaches to the media and communication as well as train the posing of theoretical questions and choosing suitable methods according the the theoretical approach.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After passing the course student - knows different classical and newer theoretical approaches to media and communication and their main concepts. 
- is able to choose an appropriate theoretical and methodological approach for solving different research problems in media and communication
